
Q4. Which method runs only once?
finish().

Q5. Why use Database.Stateful?
To preserve instance variable values between execute() invocations.

Q6. Can we make HTTP callouts in a batch?
Yes, by implementing Database.AllowsCallouts.

Q7. What is the default batch size?
200 records.

Q8. Can a batch class call another batch class?
Yes. A common pattern is to start another batch from finish() if you need sequential processing.